All Classes

Class Summary
Class
Description
Aviary
Aviary Class each aviary houses up to 5 birds of a particular type based on the regulations of the conservatory.
BirdGenerator
Bird generator Will randomly generate a bird from the prepopulated types of birds - the selection has a variety of birds from the assignment description as well as some additional ones.
Birds
Birds Class defines Birds as an abstract class The information requested are basic to most all birds -e.g final number of wings.
Conservatory
Conservatory This class houses the aviaries which in turn houses the birds that are "captured"
Main
Main driver running main will ask how many birds are needing housed - will not allow over a hundred it will auto organize the birds into the conservatory and associated aviaries.
Parrot
Parrot can speak and have vocabulary The description print out will have that additional information.
ShoreBirds
Shorebird class adds the shore of which a shorebird can be found
Waterfowl
Waterfowl similar to shorebirds adds what body of water it is near
